06638nam a22010215i 9783110950120DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20111998gw     fo  d z      ger d  a97831109501207 a10.1515/97831109501202doi  a(DE-B1597)44793  a(OCoLC)979946958  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 4aPN710b.E69 1998 7aLIT0041702bisacsh0481pa830qDE-101  aEC 54102rvk0(DE-625)rvk/20606:00aErkennen und Erinnern in Kunst und Literatur :bKolloquium Reisensburg, 4.-7. Januar 1996 /chrsg. von Wolfgang Frühwald, Peter Strohschneider, Michael Schilling, Dietmar Peil.  aReprint 2011 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2011] 4c©1998  a1 online resource (675 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDer Band versammelt Beiträge, die in interdisziplinärer Perspektive Probleme mediävistischer Memoria-Forschung, die humanistische Memorialkultur wie auch das Erinnern in neuerer und neuester Literatur behandeln. Dabei konzentrieren sich die Studien zum einen auf die problemgeschichtliche Frage nach dem Verständnis von "kulturellem Gedächtnis" und Identität einerseits sowie Fiktionalität andererseits. Zum andern thematisiert der Band das in der jüngeren Forschungsdiskussion nur peripher behandelte Verhältnis von Erinnerung und Erkenntnis.  aThe volume assembles articles taking an interdisciplinary perspective on problems of medieval studies research into the concept of memoria, the humanist culture of memoria, and remembrance as thematized in recent and contemporary literature. The studies focus first on two major topics: a) the problem of what is meant by 'cultural memory', how it ties in with identity, and the way this concept has changed through the ages; and b) fictionality. The rest of the volume is given over to a discussion of the relation between remembrance and apperception, a subject only given marginal attention in the recent research literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEuropean literaturexHistory and criticismvCongresses. 4aErinnerung ‹Motiv›. 4aGeschichte 1100-1981. 4aLiteratur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aBauer, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirus, Hendrik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBroich, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBüttner, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaly, Peter Μ., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreytag, Hartmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrühwald, Wolfgang, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGreen, Dennis Η., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaas, Alois Μ., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHogrebe, Wolfram, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaeger, C. Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJahn, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKablitz, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKleinschmidt, Erich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlose, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrämer, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Jan-Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeudeck, Otto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeumann, Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.